I"Ë=<p>This is GNU/Linux machine that contains a large number available ports, enumerate the NFS service allows us to identify the home directory to mount it on our machine, in order to add a public key and thus access the server, abuse the sudo permissions to edit the /etc/exports file allowed to get a shell with root privileges.</p>

<h2 id="information-gathering">Information Gathering</h2>
<h3 id="host-discovery">Host Discovery</h3>

<p>A ping scan detected the target machine, the script you can find it <a href="https://github.com/s4rgaz/hdiscovery.git">here</a>.</p>

<div class="language-bash highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>root@kali:~/vulnix<span class="nv">$ </span>hdiscovery.py <span class="nt">-t</span> 192.168.179.0/24
192.168.179.174 is alive
</code></pre></div></div>

